{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow a second referendum on Scottish Independence with specific qualifications",
        "additional_details": "Now is the time to allow a second vote of Scottish independence - the case for the union has never been stronger, the polls are at their lowest, and calling the pro-independence side\u2019s bluff will allow us to progress with the real issues. We cannot repeat another 5 years of national embarrassment. The following caveats should be included:\r\n\r\nMinimum age of 18\r\n\r\nNo EU/ foreign nationals\r\n\r\nScot\u2019s living in England should get a vote\r\n\r\n50% of total electorate required to win\r\n\r\nNo vote on the same issue until at least 2050",
        "background": "For the past 5 years the Scottish Government have failed to act on Scotland\u2019s behalf in devolved areas including education, health, policing and the economy (to name a few), and have neglected a mental health and drugs crisis, in favour of independence, causing national embarrassment for Scotland.",
